quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  4,58,"Allah does indeed command you to hand over the trusts to those to whom they are due, and that when you judge between people, you judge with justice. Allah does indeed give you the best of admonition. Allah does indeed hear all, see all"
  4,59,"O you who believe! Obey Allah, and obey the Messenger and those in authority from amongst you. Then if you believe in Allah and the Hereafter and quarrel on anything, refer it to Allah and the Messenger. That is better, and it is the best solution.h"
  4,60,"Have you not seen those who assert that they believe in what has been revealed to you and in what was revealed before you? They would like to go to someone who has rebelled against Allah, for judgement, although they were commanded to deny him. And the Satan desires to lead them far astray"
  4,61,"And when it is said to them, \"Come to what Allah has revealed and to the Messenger\", you see the hypocrites turning away from you in aversion"
  4,62,"Then, how about it, when a calamity befalls them on account of what they did before, and they come to you swearing by Allah, \"We did not desire anything but goodwill and amity"
  4,63,"Allah knows what is there in their inner minds. So leave them alone, admonish them, and speak to them words that would touch their inner souls"
  4,64,"And We did not send any Messenger but to be obeyed by Allah's command. And if only they had — when they were unjust to themselves — come to you and asked forgiveness of Allah and the Messenger asked forgiveness for them, they would have found Allah Accepting repentance, Merciful"
  4,65,"No! By your Lord, no! They believe not, until they make you the arbiter in disputes among them, and then find no reservations in their minds on your decisions and submit to them entirely"
  4,66,"And if We had passed an order for them to lay down their lives or to leave their homes, they would not have done it, except for a few of them. And had they done what they were advised to, it would have certainly been better for them and it would have very much strengthened their position"
  4,67,"And in that case, We would certainly have given them from Ourselves a great reward"
  4,68,And We would certainly have guided them to the Straight Path
  4,69,"And persons like the one who obeys Allah and the Messenger, are in the company of the prophets, the truthful, the martyrs and the righteous, upon whom Allah has bestowed rewards. And how excellent are these companions"
  4,70,"This is the favour from Allah, and sufficient is Allah, the Embodiment of all knowledge"
  4,71,"O you who believe! Be on your guard, and then go out in strength or all together"
  4,72,"And, indeed, among you certainly is he who would drop behind! If then a calamity befalls you, he says, \"Surely Allah conferred a benefit on me that I was not present with them"
  4,73,"And if you do get a favour from Allah, he would certainly say, as if you were not on friendly terms with him, \"Oh! I wish I had been with them. I would then achieve a great success"